column4:
…this study suggests three simple points for clinicians. Firstly,
there is considerable potential for offending older men by
making assumptions about their sexual behaviour or motivation.
Older couples may not differ substantially from younger couples
in sexual interest or activity.49 Secondly, phosphodiesterase type
5 inhibitors are not a panacea. Thirdly, the majority of men are
not going to ask for help with erectile dysfunction and therefore
it may be necessary for someone in the clinical team to explore
this sensitively but routinely...
column5: …better training could improve this situation, as might the reorganisation of services…
